The paper deals with the Voronoi diagram, a fundamental topic in computational geometry, which is covered in the cs.CG sub-category. The paper also analyzes the combinatorial complexity of the diagram, which falls under the cs.DS sub-category. The paper also discusses the iterative approach to construct the diagram, which is related to the cs.DM sub-category. The paper also considers the $L_p$ metric, which is relevant to the cs.GR sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses the issue of non-uniqueness for $k$-nearest sites, which is related to the cs.SI sub-category.
